{{Transcript|quest}}
{{Transcript list|Almera|Gerald|Hudon|Hadley|Golrie}}

==Starting out==
===Boarding raft before starting quest===
* {{tbox|You're not sure if the raft is safe to use. Best to leave it alone.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hudon while standing near the house===
* {{tbox|Hudon can't hear you because of the noise of the waterfall. Perhaps the acoustics would be better from that island?}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Almera===
* '''Player:''' Hello.
* '''Almera:''' Ah, hello there. Nice to see an outsider for a change. Are you busy? I have a problem.
* {{tcond|With a combat level lower than 25:}}
** {{tbox|Before starting this quest, be aware that your combat level is lower than the recommended level of 25.}}
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tselect|Start the Waterfall Quest?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** '''Player:''' How can I help?
** '''Almera:''' It's my son Hudon, he's always getting into trouble. The boy's convinced there's hidden treasure in the river and I'm a bit worried about his safety, the poor lad can't even swim.
** '''Player:''' I could go and take a look for you if you like?
** '''Almera:''' Would you? You are kind. You can use the small raft out back if you wish, do be careful, the current down stream is very strong.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm afraid I'm in a rush.
** '''Almera:''' Oh okay, never mind.
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Almera again====
* '''Player:''' Hello Almera.
* '''Almera:''' Hello adventurer, have you seen my boy yet?
* '''Player:''' I'm afraid not, but I'm sure he hasn't gone far.
* '''Almera:''' I do hope so, you can't be too careful these days.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Gerald====
* '''Player:''' Hello.
* '''Gerald:''' Hello there.
* '''Player:''' Have you seen a small boy?
* '''Gerald:''' Nope, plenty of small fish though.
* {{tact|end}}

===Using the raft===
* {{tbox|You board the small raft and push off down stream...}}
* {{tbox|...you crash into a small island.}}
* '''Player:''' Hello son, are you okay? You need help?
* '''Hudon:''' It looks like you need the help.
* '''Player:''' Your mum sent me to find you.
* '''Hudon:''' Don't play nice with me, I know you're looking for the treasure too.
* '''Player:''' Where is this treasure you talk of?
* '''Hudon:''' Just because I'm small doesn't mean I'm dumb! If I told you, you would take it all for yourself.
* '''Player:''' Maybe I could help.
* '''Hudon:''' I'm fine alone.
* '''Player:''' Hmm... I wonder what this treasure is.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hudon again===
* '''Player:''' So you're still here.
* '''Hudon:''' I'll find that treasure soon, just you wait and see.
* {{tact|end}}

===Swimming to the rock===
* {{tbox|You swim out into the water...}}
* {{tbox|...but the current is too strong, washing you downstream.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Getting washed down the waterfall after talking to Hudon===
* '''Gerald:''' Blimey! Where did you come from? Not another one of those treasure hunters are you?
* '''Player:''' Treasure hunters?
* '''Gerald:''' They say there's treasure hidden within the waterfall, left behind by the old elven king. Not that anyone's ever found anything.
* '''Player:''' Interesting, is there somewhere I can learn more about this?
* '''Gerald:''' You could ask Hadley the tourist guide. He'll be in this building just here.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Almera after talking to Hudon===
* '''Player:''' Hello again.
* '''Almera:''' Well hello, you're still around then.
* '''Player:''' I saw Hudon by the river but he refused to come back with me.
* '''Almera:''' Yes he told me, the foolish lad came in drenched to the bone, he had fallen into the waterfall, lucky he wasn't killed! Now he can spend the rest of the summer in his room.
* '''Player:''' Any ideas what I could do while I'm here?
* '''Almera:''' Why don't you visit the tourist centre south of the waterfall?
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Gerald again before learning about the treasure===
* '''Player:''' Hello.
* '''Gerald:''' Hello traveller. Are you here to fish or to hunt for treasure?
* '''Player:''' Why do you say that?
* '''Gerald:''' Adventurers pass through here every week, they never find anything though.
* '''Player:''' What treasure are they looking for?
* '''Gerald:''' They say there's treasure hidden within the waterfall, left behind by the old elven king. Not that anyone's ever found anything.
* '''Player:''' Interesting, is there somewhere I can learn more about this?
* '''Gerald:''' You could ask Hadley the tourist guide. He'll be in this building just here.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hadley===
* '''Player:''' Hello there.
* '''Hadley:''' Are you on holiday? If so you've come to the right place. I'm Hadley the tourist guide, anything you need to know just ask me. We have some of the most unspoilt wildlife and scenery in Gielinor.
* '''Hadley:''' People come from miles around to fish in the clear lakes or to wander the beautiful hillsides.
* '''Player:''' It is quite pretty.
* '''Hadley:''' Surely pretty is an understatement kind sir. Beautiful, amazing or possibly life-changing would be more suitable wording. Have you seen Baxtorian Falls? Named after the elven king who was buried beneath them.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me what happened to the elven king?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you tell me what happened to the elven king?
** '''Hadley:''' Baxtorian? I guess he died a long long time ago, it's quite sad really. After leaving his kingdom to deal with invading forces, Baxtorian returned to find his wife Glarial had been captured by the enemy.
** '''Hadley:''' This destroyed Baxtorian, after years of searching he became a recluse. He went into the secret home he had made for Glarial under the waterfall and sealed himself in. To this day, no one has managed to enter.
** '''Hadley:''' Anyway, I believe we have a book on him upstairs if you want to learn more.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Where else is worth visiting around here?}}
** '''Player:''' Where else is worth visiting around here?
** '''Hadley:''' There is a lovely spot for a picnic on the hill to the north east, there's a monument to the elven queen Glarial. It really is quite pretty.
** '''Player:''' Who was Glarial?
** '''Hadley:''' Baxtorian's wife, the only other person who could also enter the waterfall apart from him. She was queen when this land was inhabited by elven kind.
** '''Hadley:''' Glarial was kidnapped while Baxtorian was away, but they eventually recovered her body and brought her home to rest.
** '''Player:''' That's sad.
** '''Hadley:''' True, I believe we have a book on Baxtorian and Glarial upstairs if you want to learn more.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Is there treasure under the waterfall?}}
** '''Player:''' Is there treasure under the waterfall?
** '''Hadley:''' Ha ha... Another treasure hunter. Well if there is no one's been able to get to it. They've been searching that river for decades, all to no avail.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Thanks, goodbye.}}
** '''Player:''' Thanks, goodbye.
** '''Hadley:''' Enjoy your visit.
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching the correct bookcase===
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the book:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Book on baxtorian detail.png|You find a book named 'Book on Baxtorian' on the bookcase.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player already has the book:}}
** {{mes|You search the bookcase but find nothing of interest}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching an incorrect bookcase===
* {{mes|You search the books...}}
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
** {{mes|You don't find anything that you'd ever want to read.}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
** {{mes|You find nothing to interest you.}}
* {{topt|Dialogue 3}}
** {{mes|None of them look very interesting}}

===Talking to Almera after reading the book===
* '''Player:''' Hello again Almera.
* '''Almera:''' Well hello again brave adventurer, are you enjoying the tranquil scenery of these parts?
* '''Player:''' Yes, very relaxing.
* '''Almera:''' Well I'm glad to hear it{{sic|Missing period}} The authorities wanted to dig up this whole area for a mine, but the few locals who lived here wouldn't budge and they gave up.
* '''Player:''' Good for you.
* '''Almera:''' Good for all of us!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hudon after reading the book===
* '''Player:''' Hello Hudon.
* '''Hudon:''' Oh it's you, trying to find my treasure again are you?
* '''Player:''' I didn't know it belonged to you.
* '''Hudon:''' It will do when I find it. I just need to get into this blasted waterfall I've been washed downstream three times already.
* {{tact|end}}

==Obtaining the pebble==
===Opening door to Golrie from the outside===
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have the key:}}
** '''Player:''' Hello, are you okay?
** '''Golrie:''' It's just those blasted hob-gobs. I locked myself in here for protection. But I've left the key somewhere and now I'm stuck.
** '''Player:''' Okay... I'll have a look for a key.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the key:}}
** {{mes|You use the key to unlock the gate.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Opening door to Golrie from the inside===
* {{mes|You open the gate and walk through.}}

===Searching the crate with the key===
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have the key:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Key (Tree Gnome Village Dungeon) detail.png|You find a key in the crate.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the key:}}
** {{mes|You search the crate but find nothing of interest.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Golrie===
* '''Player:''' Hello, who are you?
* '''Golrie:''' I'm Golrie, I've been stuck in here for ages. those hob-gobs are trying to steal my family's heirlooms. My grandad gave me all sorts of old junk.
* '''Player:''' Do you mind if I have a look?
* '''Golrie:''' No, of course not.
* {{tbox|pic=Glarial's pebble detail.png|You look amongst the junk on the floor and find Glarial's pebble.}}
* '''Player:''' Could I take this old pebble?
* '''Golrie:''' Oh that, yes have it, it's just some old elven junk I believe.
* '''Golrie:''' Thanks a lot for the key traveller. I think I'll wait in here until those hob-gobs get bored and leave. {{^|Note: still says this even if the player dropped the key.}}
* '''Player:''' Okay, take care Golrie.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Golrie again====
* '''Player:''' Hello Golrie.
* '''Golrie:''' Hello again.
* '''Player:''' Do you mind if I have another look through this stuff?
* '''Golrie:''' No, of course not.
* {{tcond|If the player already has the pebble:}}
** {{tbox|You look amongst the junk on the floor but find nothing of interest.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Glarial's pebble detail.png|You look amongst the junk on the floor and find Glarial's pebble but you don't have enough room to take it.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tbox|pic=Glarial's pebble detail.png|You look amongst the junk on the floor and find Glarial's pebble.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using Glarial's pebble on Glarial's Tombstone===
* {{tcond|If the player has disallowed items:}}
** {{tbox|You place the pebble in the gravestone's small indent but nothing happens.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no disallowed items:}}
** {{tbox|You place the pebble in the gravestone's small indent. The stone slab slides back revealing a ladder. You climb down it.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching the chest===
* {{tcond|If the player does not have Glarial's amulet:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Glarial's amulet detail.png|You find a small amulet in the chest.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player already has Glarial's amulet:}}
** {{mes|You search the chest but find nothing.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching Glarial's Tomb===
* {{tcond|If the player does not have Glarial's urn:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Glarial's urn detail.png|You find an urn full of ashes in the tomb.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player already has Glarial's urn:}}
** {{mes|You search the tomb but find nothing.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Almera after visiting Glarial's tomb===
* '''Player:''' Hello Almera.
* '''Almera:''' Hello adventurer, how's your treasure hunt going?
* '''Player:''' Oh, I'm just sight seeing.
* '''Almera:''' No adventurer stays here this long just to sight see. But your business is yours alone, if you need to use the raft go ahead. But please try not crash it this time!{{sic|Missing "to"}}
* '''Player:''' Thanks Almera.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hudon after visiting Glarial's tomb===
* '''Player:''' Hello again.
* '''Hudon:''' Not you still, why don't you give up?
* '''Player:''' And miss all the fun!
* '''Hudon:''' You do understand that anything you find you have to share with me.
* '''Player:''' Why's that?
* '''Hudon:''' Because I told you about the treasure.
* '''Player:''' Well, I wouldn't count on it.
* '''Hudon:''' That's not fair.
* '''Player:''' Neither is life kid.
* {{tact|end}}

==Accessing the Waterfall Dungeon==
===Climbing the Dead Tree===
* {{tbox|You try to use the tree to climb down...}}
* {{tbox|...but you slip and fall into the water.}}
* '''Player:''' {{overhead|Ouch!}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using rope on the Dead Tree===
* {{tbox|You tie the rope to the tree and climb down to the ledge below.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Climbing in the barrel===
* {{tbox|You climb into the barrel and push off the edge. You are carried down the river.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Opening the door to the Waterfall dungeon===
* {{tcond|If the player is wearing Glarial's amulet:}}
** {{tbox|You enter the waterfall.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player is not wearing Glarial's amulet:}}
** {{tbox|You try to open the door, but the ledge is suddenly flooded with water...}}
** {{tbox|...you are pushed over the waterfall and into the river.}}
** '''Player:''' {{overhead|Ouch!}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Leaving the Waterfall dungeon===
* {{tbox|You exit the dungeon.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Opening the door to Baxtorian's tomb===
* {{tcond|If the player has the key:}}
** {{mes|You use the key to unlock the door.}}
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the key:}}
** {{mes|The door is locked.}}

===Searching the crate in the Waterfall dungeon===
* {{tcond|If the player does not have the key:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Key (Waterfall Dungeon) detail.png|You find a key in the crate.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player already has the key:}}
** {{mes|You search the crate but find nothing of interest.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Using runes on the pillars===
* {{tcond|If the player has already placed that rune on that pillar:}}
** {{mes|You've already put that type of rune on this pillar.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player used an air rune:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Air rune detail.png|You place the rune on the pillar. It disappears in a puff of smoke.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player used an earth rune:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Earth rune detail.png|You place the rune on the pillar. It disappears in a puff of smoke.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player used a water rune:}}
** {{tbox|pic=Water rune detail.png|You place the rune on the pillar. It disappears in a puff of smoke.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Using Glarial's amulet on the Statue of Glarial===
* {{tcond|If the player has not yet placed all the runes on the pillars:}}
** {{tbox|You go to place the amulet around the neck of the statue. However, water floods into the room as you do...}}
** {{tbox|...you are washed out of the cave and down the river.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has placed all the runes:}}
** {{tbox|You place the amulet around the neck of the statue. You hear a loud rumble from beneath as the floor rises.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Take treasure from the chalice===
* {{tbox|You go to take the treasure from the chalice. However, water floods into the room as you do...}}
* {{tbox|...you are washed out of the cave and down the river.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Using Glarial's urn on the chalice===
* {{tbox|You carefully pour the ashes into the chalice and remove Baxtorian's treasure...}}
* {{qact|Congratulations! Quest complete!}}

==Post-quest==
===Take treasure from the chalice===
* {{tbox|The chalice only contains some old ashes.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Hudon after the quest===
* '''Player:''' Hello again.
* '''Hudon:''' You stole my treasure. I saw you!
* '''Player:''' I'll make sure it goes to a good cause.
* '''Hudon:''' Hmmmm!
* {{tact|end}}

